<br>
re:  f/u on interuption testing<br>
<br>
I decided to mix up a half dozen &quot;Spirit of Sloths&quot; this weekend to see if in fact it got fixed.<br>
<br>
Applied my first one, purposely moved as I hit attack.<br>
<br>
Result: Interuption<br>
<br>
Applied a 2nd one, purposely moved as I hit attack:<br>
<br>
Result: Interuption<br>
<br>
Applied 3rd one, purposely did NOT move<br>
<br>
Result: Landed<br>
<br>
After finding that they really haven't been fixed it I immediately, as I usually do, sent a petitition stating: &quot;I just applied a poison and it keeps getting interupted&quot;<br>
<br>
(I've never gotten a response, but do it anyway) - I also send /bug and email Verant.<br>
<br>
About 5 minutes later, to my surprise, (and the groups surprise), a GM pops down right next to our group. He tells me to apply another poison and asks me to repeat the process. I again apply another poison, purposely move, and again interuption. I send him a tell back and say, &quot;Did ya see that?&quot;. He says, &quot;No. I didn't see it fail&quot;. I said, &quot;Well, it failed on my end&quot;. He says, &quot;Please submit a /bug report and I'll note it on my end, but this might be something to do with filtering&quot;.<br>
<br>
Filtering causing the problems? thoughts?  <p><html>

